tafsir[11]{c,v,t}:
  78,1,"Concerning what are they disputing?"
  78,3,"About which they cannot agree."
  78,7,"And the mountains as pegs?"
  78,11,"And made the day as a means of subsistence?"
  78,13,"And placed (therein) a Light of Splendour?"
  78,16,"And gardens of luxurious growth?"
  78,22,"For the transgressors a place of destination:"
  78,23,"They will dwell therein for ages."
  78,26,"A fitting recompense (for them)."
  78,28,"But they (impudently) treated Our Signs as false."
  78,29,"And all things have We preserved on record."